  <context>
    <background>
      The `AnalysisChatContextResolver` stub was created in R1 as a placeholder — it returns all
      capabilities for every session regardless of the actual playbook or entity. This means every
      SprkChat session gets the same tools, which is wrong. R2 replaces the stub with real queries
      so that:
      - An analysis using the "Legal Research" playbook gets legal research tools
      - An analysis using the "Contract Drafting" playbook gets drafting tools
      - Matter sessions get matter-scoped scope commands
      - Project sessions get project-scoped scope commands

      The resolver is the connective tissue that assembles the full chat context: capabilities
      (what the AI can do), commands (what slash commands the user sees), documents (document IDs
      in scope), search guidance (how web search is scoped), and entity context (matter/entity data
      for grounding the AI's responses).

      This task is sequential (not in a parallel group) because it depends on both `DynamicCommandResolver`
      (R2-019) and the Dataverse schema changes (R2-001). Task R2-021 (ScopeCapabilitiesService) will
      further integrate with this resolver.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      Depends on Task R2-001 (Dataverse schema — sprk_capabilities, sprk_searchGuidance, sprk_recordType fields)
      and R2-019 (DynamicCommandResolver must exist for command catalog integration). Sequential — cannot
      run in parallel with any task it depends on. Task R2-021 (ScopeCapabilities) depends on this task.
      Own files: `AnalysisChatContextResolver.cs` only — no new files needed (stub replacement).
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0">Read the full current `AnalysisChatContextResolver.cs` to understand what the stub returns and what the `ChatAnalysisContext` model looks like</step>
    <step order="1">Read `PlaybookChatContextProvider.cs` to understand how analysis context is consumed and what fields are expected</step>
    <step order="2">Read `.claude/patterns/dataverse/entity-operations.md` to confirm query patterns for related entity lookups</step>
    <step order="3">Implement Step 1: query `sprk_analysisoutput` → `sprk_analysisplaybookid` → `sprk_analysisplaybook` capabilities using Dataverse lookup expansion ($expand)</step>
    <step order="4">Implement Step 2: query the matter/entity record using `ChatHostContext.EntityType` and `ChatHostContext.RecordId` for entity-specific context fields</step>
    <step order="5">Implement Step 3: call `DynamicCommandResolver.ResolveCommandsAsync(context)` to get the command catalog; query active scopes for `sprk_searchGuidance` and `sprk_capabilities`</step>
    <step order="6">Implement Step 4: assemble the `ChatAnalysisContext` from all gathered data</step>
    <step order="7">Implement Redis caching: serialize assembled context to JSON, store with key `chat-context:{tenantId}:{sessionId}` and 30-minute TTL</step>
    <step order="8">Add cache-first check at method entry: return cached context if found</step>
    <step order="9">Replace the stub body entirely — ensure the stub's "return all capabilities" behavior is removed</step>
    <step order="10">Run `dotnet build` and verify no errors</step>
    <step order="11">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change task R2-020 status to completed (🔲 → ✅)</step>
  </steps>

