  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Sessions using the "Legal Research" playbook return only legal research capabilities in the context (not all capabilities)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Sessions using the "Contract Drafting" playbook return only contract drafting capabilities</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">ChatAnalysisContext includes `SearchGuidance` from the active scope's `sprk_searchGuidance` field (not empty for scopes that have it configured)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Second call with same sessionId returns result from Redis (cache hit) within 100ms (NFR-03 with cache)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Redis key `chat-context:{tenantId}:{sessionId}` exists after first resolution with 30-minute TTL</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Entity context includes matter-specific data (e.g., matter name) for matter-based sessions</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No entity field values (matter names, case details) appear in logs at Info or higher (ADR-015)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`dotnet build` passes with no errors</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The `ChatAnalysisContext` model may need new fields if the stub model did not include
    `SearchGuidance`, `ScopeMetadata`, or `EntityContext`. If model changes are needed, check
    all callers of the resolver to ensure they handle the new fields gracefully (backward
    compatibility via optional/nullable fields).

    The Dataverse query for `sprk_analysisoutput` → playbook lookup may require understanding
    the relationship structure. Check `ChatDataverseRepository.cs` (if it exists) or the existing
    Dataverse query patterns in other BFF services for how lookup navigation is handled in OData
    queries for this project.

    If the scope association with analysis/matter is not yet established in the Dataverse schema,
    query all active scopes for the tenant as a fallback. Document this assumption in the
    `notes/020-context-resolver-queries.md` for the Dataverse architect to review.
  </notes>

